FBIS4-35347 "drnes104_j_94062" FBIS-NES-94-104 Daily Report 27 May 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Ground-to-Ground Missile Attacks on Aden Continue Ground-to-Ground Missile Attacks on Aden Continue EA2705191494 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network in Arabic 1500 GMT 27 May 94 EA2705191494 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network in Arabic 1500 GMT 27 May 94 Arabic BFN [Text] A responsible military source at the Command of the Armed Forces of the Democratic Republic of Yemen has said that the ruling Sanaa gang, at the same time that it claims it wishes to reach a cease-fire, is continuing its practice of misleading Arab and international public opinion. Yesterday evening it fired another ground-to-ground missile toward the capital, Aden. The source confirmed to the Yemeni news agency, SABA', that our vigilant ground defenses destroyed it in the air. Its parts fell in one of the farms in the Lahij Governorate, causing no deaths or material damage.
